## v1.4.0 (2026-04-25)

**Changed by:** ProjectTelemachy myrmidon-swarm pass (2026-04-25)
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed
- Added deterministic classification rule (skip classifier swarm when inventory has file evidence)
- Added per-file mega-agent rule in Phase 2 plan design
- Added parallel Plan agent + Explore agents optimization note to Phase 2
- Added HARD issues enumeration note and PR title length note to Phase 7
- Added session stats: 57→6 issues, 17 PRs, ~2.5h wall clock (ProjectTelemachy table)
- Added Verified On row: ProjectTelemachy 2026-04-25
- Added Failed Attempts entry: running Phase 4 classifier swarm when inventory already has file evidence
- Added mega-agent candidate bash commands to Quick Reference
- Bumped version 1.3.0 → 1.4.0

### Why
Running 3 classifier agents after 3 inventory agents had already returned file paths was redundant.
Classification from file-contention counts is deterministic and faster. Per-file mega-agents
collapsed 12 planned waves to 2 (Wave D: 3 parallel + Wave E: 1 solo), saving ~90 min. Simultaneous
Phase 0 + Wave A + Wave B dispatch (12 agents in one message) also saved a full phase of serial
execution.

