## v1.2.0 (2026-04-23)

**Changed by:** ProjectArgus branch/worktree cleanup session
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed
- Added Failed Attempts entry: `git worktree remove` blocked by `__pycache__` untracked files
- Added Phase 5 cleanup note: clean `__pycache__` with `find` before `git worktree remove`

### Why
After a batch triage session, `git worktree remove` failed on all 5 unlocked worktrees due to `__pycache__/` dirs left by Python execution in agents. Safety Net also blocks `--force`. Fix: clean `__pycache__` first.

---

## v1.0.0 — 2026-04-05

### Snapshot

```
---
name: myrmidon-swarm-end-to-end-orchestration-full-workflow
description: "Full end-to-end L0 commander pattern for complex myrmidon orchestration sessions. Use when: (1) task spans 3+ phases (cleanup + rebase + merge + CI + knowledge), (2) 10+ sub-tasks with mixed agent tiers required, (3) cross-repo work requiring /advise and /learn coordination, (4) feedback loops and decision gates are needed before committing to destructive operations, (5) auto-merge assumption cannot be made (CI may fail)."
